The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 9: Driven by corporation and customs tax collections, tax revenues (excluding services tax) of the government grew 31.71 per cent at Rs 95,538 crore during the first four months of this fiscal against Rs 72,521 crore during the corresponding period of 2005-06. Of these, direct taxes contributed Rs 36,081 crore, up 61.12 per cent, while indirect taxes (excluding services tax) chipped in Rs 59,457 crore, higher by 18.6 per cent over the April-June period of 2005-06.

 Mumbai, Aug. 9: Canara Bank today said it will raise Rs 3,000 crore in the current fiscal through a combination of debt and equity instruments with a part of it likely to come through a follow-on public offer within the calendar year. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 9: The Reserve Bank of India today released certain modifications to its previously announced guidelines for banks undertaking primary dealer (PD) business. The RBI stated it would not be necessary for banks to maintain a separate subsidiary general ledger account, as notified earlier, for the PD business.

 Mumbai, Aug. 9: VSNL today said its promoter group company Tata Sons has increased its stake in the company to 5.64 per cent.

 New Delhi, Aug. 9: Petronet LNG will offer up to 10 per cent stake in the company to a strategic investor who is willing to supply LNG to it.




